  "response": "Yes, money laundering is a serious financial crime. It involves concealing the origins of illegally obtained money by passing it through legitimate businesses or bank accounts to make it appear legal. Money laundering is illegal in most countries and can result in significant criminal penalties, including:\n\n1. Fines\n2. Prison sentences\n3. Asset seizure\n\nThe process typically involves three stages:\n- Placement (introducing illegal money into the financial system)\n- Layering (concealing the source through complex transactions)\n- Integration (making the money appear legitimate)\n\nMoney laundering is often associated with other criminal activities like drug trafficking, fraud, and organized crime.",
